 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Cuku</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> There are many good items if you are lvl 44 or lower, I won't list individual items, but you can see a running list that being updated on the general message board at <a href="http://www.graffe.com/" target="_blank">http://www.graffe.com/</a></P><P>I would think if you can get the following types of items then you will be alot more powerful than I was at lower levels :) My suggestions are based on mana management, not on increased damage on DD's. So my preferences/reccomendation in order of priority would be:</P><P>Afflicition Efficiency</P><P>Extended Afflicition</P><P>Mana Conservation (for those spells that are not dots)</P><P>Spell Haste</P><P>Improved Damage</P><P>All of those items with focus I or II on them are pretty easily camped, or bought, so if you are casting spells of lvl 44 or lower you will be set :)</P><P>However, if you are casting necro spells over 44 you are basically screwed.</P><P>The majority of the focus III items are the rare drops on Uber mobs, so while this focus patch was a great concept. It basically was a twink patch. Focus I and II have exactly the same effcts on spells for their lvl ranges as focus III does. But the availability of Focus III items is so much rarer. Much better off spending time and working on Spell Casting Mastery AA skill and just hope you get lucky on raids and a focus item you can use will drop.</P><P>A couple annoying facts about focus item effects atm seem to be:</P><P>The focus effect is random and not fixed, even tho VI says its fixed.</P><P>Ext Afflicition does not work with life tap dots.</P><P>Improved Damage effect (or magi focus items) does not see ignite bones, incinerate bone, chill bones, conglacitation of bones, insidious retro as DD spells.</P><P>Group buffs thru tap spells such as Degeneration, Mind wrack, Crippling, are not considered buffs so extended enhancement doesnt work with them.</P><P>Healing dot spells like Shadowbond, Zeveers etc are not considered heal spells for improved healing focus.</P><P>And our treasured mana transfer spell doesnt seem to fall into a buff catagory either (personal peive of mine, that a spell we use so much still sucks so bad on the transfer rate 400 of my mana for 150 to someone else and a long recast time. Come on, wtf at least they could reduce refresh time, or make a lvl 59 AA skill for it like they did for cannabalize for shamans. And get rid of the lvl 59 AA mass group buff that we cant use anyway!</P><P>With all that said :) I think the best single item you can try for in non raid groups will be the Oblus Death Shroud, it's only 10% mana reduction, but at least its a item thats obtainable now. That is after you fight for the camp :)</P><P><BR>Cuku<BR>59 Iksar Necro<BR>FV Server (Fire & Fury)<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223050" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223050</a> </P><P><BR> </font></td>
